profile_positions.description:
As a digital data analyst (a.i. for 18 months), I have made data generated through various digital channels intelligible for both marketing and sales departments within NNIP. I have unlocked various sources such as Google Analytics, LinkedIn, Twitter, Pardot (email), Salesforce (CRM), Google Data Studio (Paid Media) and websites using Python, Power BI and Salesforce Einstein Analytics. In parallel with above, I have improved and prepared the data to create various robust dashboards, such as for example;

- Social Media Dashboard | PowerBI | users can make trends and insights at both a global and detailed level intelligible in an easy and attractive way for Twitter and LinkedIn;

‒	Online Media Dashboard | PowerBI | users have a powerful tool to closely monitor an external (online) media agency and quickly make the effectiveness of the online media budget intelligible at global and at detailed level (per country, digital channel, medium, websites/partners, campaign, advertisement);

‒	Sales Priority Dashboard | Einstein Analytics | developed an universe with recipes, which created a bridge between marketing (email) activities within Pardot and sales activities within Salesforce. The interactive dashboard on top of that universe provide users a real-time 360-degree view of both existing and potential accounts and all underlying personal profiles. The engagement of not only existing contacts but also prospects and leads from Pardot are taken into consideration. Engagement over time at multiple and different levels such as country, sales entity, defined segments, accounts and contacts are easy to generate. Even per strategy, campaign, subject or kind of content. Easy to use for qualifying prospects or leads and monitoring open opportunities, contacts or accounts by providing combined overviews of marketing- and sales activities and the resulted engagement.

‒	Tools/skills: Python / Pardot / Salesforce / Einstein Analytics / SQL / Power BI

‒ As Product Owner Marketing Makers team lead of the Scrum team consisting of 7 FTEs, of which 3 work in NL and 4 in India. Responsible for the technical and commercial optimization of the KPN webshop for mobile phones and subscriptions and the NS webshop Discover Holland. In addition, I functioned as a central point of contact for external clients for new assignments / projects and progress on other, internal digital solutions within KPN and NS;

- As a database analyst within Basedriver (supplier of an email software solution for large publishers including Hearst & NSM) responsible for reports and analyzes on large data collections to provide insight into acquisition, (future) churn and engagement at segment level. I have also developed machine learning algorithms to determine the best sending moment of emails per profile, which increases open and click rates; 

- Tools/skills: MongoDB / SQL / Python / Microsoft Power BI en Google Data Studio.

‒ As CRM Manager responsible for activation and retention of all car dealers that advertise with AutoTrack. For this purpose I have redesigned applications such as SalesForce, analysed and developed database / retention reports and improved emails sent to dealers via Selligent; 

‒ As a Business Analyst developed various algorithms, so that visitors to the AutoTrack platform will see the most popular occasions first. Algorithms have been developed on the basis of combining data sources, including the online click and search behaviour and the turnover rate at which used cars were sold. By placing different cookies and using Elasticsearch, AutoTrack was able to test and develop four different algorithms simultaneously on the platform (+ 11%); 

‒ Tools/skills: SalesForce / SQL / Python / Business Objects / DevOps project management / Google Data Studio & Analytics.

‒ ad interim manager marketing & communications department (6 FTE) and responsible for the sale of individual tickets (+ 15%) and season tickets (+ 7%) during the second half of the season;

‒ online reach increased with e-mail, social media (Facebook) and affiliates. Online conversion increases by adjusting landing pages and order forms; 

‒ database analysis (RFM / penetration) to increase the loyalty and customer value of season ticket holders and recruit new supporters with targeted actions. Also provided support with the implementation of the database platform.

Budgetary responsible for various services for which I have developed annual marketing plans and implemented campaigns and actions to acquire consumers and increase sales to existing customers:

=>  2014 – 2015		fixed telephony, interactive television and Video On Demand
- database analyzes (SQL) to accurately predict the declining, but substantial turnover per month on telephony for management;
- developed the interactive TV marketing database together with IT and prepared reports for monitoring KPIs. In addition, based on (customer) insights set up all kinds of activation and retention campaigns.

=> 2011 – 2013		ESPN (FOX Sports / Eredivisie Live) / HBO (launch premium channel) / erotic
- as project manager migrated Eredivisie Live subscribers to FOX Sports Totaal. The chosen approach was successful, so that the penetration of FOX Sports was no less than 50% higher than that of the competition (2013 - Q3 / Q4);
- as project manager launched HBO (new premium channel) within Ziggo. The design of the campaign and proposition resulted in 70,000 subscribers within 4 months (2012 - Q2 / Q3).

=> 2008 – 2011		online marketing (all services)
- within marketing team Get responsible for SEA, SEO, online display, e-tailers and affiliate marketing; 
- manage external agencies such as Traffic4u (search engine optimization) and TradeDoubler (implement and monitor affiliate program); 
- developed a conversion attribution model using tagging data. Through links and operations on various data files (SQL) I have been able to determine the commercial value of online resources. This provided valuable management information.

- manager team MarCom (2 employees communication: call center & online);
- responsible for commercial policy;
- defining and implementing marketing and communication plans to both acquire and retain customers;
- setting up joint campaigns with both hardware manufacturers and other external parties / advertisers;
- develop and implement online market research.

- responsible for the commercial policy and marketing and communication plans to both acquire and retain customers;

=>mapped the causes of high churn with database analysis (SQL). An important cause was the less than optimal registration and payment processes. As a project leader of a large team, I was able to successfully change these processes (+ 50% retention uplift at 90 days); 

=> Developed a welcome program designed to increase both usage (+ 8%) and loyalty (+ 3%) within the first 90 days.

- initiating and supervising database marketing projects at large organizations, such as insurers and banks;
- supervising a long-term internal database marketing course at ING Bank; 
- giving the trimester course Marketing & Management at the University of Amsterdam (UVA).
